ensus that the war was fought, or should be fought, for the cause of Union, there was bitter disagreement over how to define that cause-debate not only between political camps but also within them. The chapters touch on economics, politics, culture, military affairs, ethnicity, and questions relating to just war.Contributors: Michael T. Caires, Frank Cirillo, D.H. Dilbeck, Jack Furniss, Jesse George-Nichol, William B. Kurtz, Peter C. Luebke, and Tamika Nunley  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jul 2020) 0aPolitical culturezUnited StatesxHistoryy19th century. 4aDemocratic Party. 4aRepublican Party. 4aUnion. 4aemancipation. 4anationalism. 4apolitics. 7aHISTORY / United States / Civil War Period (1850-1877).2bisacsh1 aCaires, Michael1 aCirillo, Frank1 aDilbeck, D.H.1 aFurniss, Jack1 aGallagher, Gary W.1 aGallagher, Gary W., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGeorge-Nichol, Jesse1 aKurtz, William B.1 aLuebke, Peter1 aNunley, Tamika1 aVaron, Elizabeth R.1 aVaron, Elizabeth R., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertFUP eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311070729840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780823284566zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780823284566423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780823284566.jpg  a978-3-11-070729-8  FUP eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK